Tuberculous Prostatitis,"Chronic urinary symptoms; Hematuria; Perineal pain; Systemic TB symptoms (fever, weight loss, night sweats)","Adults, especially in regions with higher TB prevalence",History of tuberculosis elsewhere; Immunosuppression; HIV
Fungal Prostatitis,Urinary frequency/urgency; Dysuria; Pelvic pain; Fever in systemic infection,More common in immunocompromised patients of any adult age,"Immunosuppression (HIV, transplant, steroids); Diabetes; Recent broad-spectrum antibiotics"
Viral Prostatitis,"Urinary discomfort; Pelvic pain; Systemic viral symptoms depending on virus (fever, malaise)",More common in immunocompromised; can affect adults of various ages,Recent viral infections; Immunosuppression
